title: Michigan St Spartans vs. Rutgers Scarlet Knights Pick Prediction NCAA College Football Point Spread Over Under Money Line Betting Odds Preview 10-10-2015
text:
Point Spread Odds: Michigan St -13 ½ points 
Over Under Total: 52 
Money Line: Michigan St -500 odds and Rutgers +400 odds 
Notes: Last year in their meeting it was Michigan St with the 45-5 home victory as a -24 point wagering favorite with the total going under 57 ½ points. Michigan St is 5-0 with the 24-21 home victory last week to the Purdue Boilermakers as a -23 point wagering favorite. The total went under 53 points. The Spartans run game worked as the team ran for 267 yards and averaged over 5 ½ yards per carry. They had a +3 turnover margin. Michigan St is 86th in the nation in total offense by averaging 379 yards per game. 
Rutgers is 2-2 following the 27-14 home victory last week to the Kansas Jayhawks as a -13 ½ point wagering favorite. The total went under 62 ½ points. The Scarlet Knights had 513 yards of offense with their run game producing 312 yards for 5 ½ yards per run attempt. Rutgers rank 26th in the country against the run by allowing 118 yards per game on the ground.
